        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 6:24PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lubbock International Airport, or 8 miles northeast of Lubbock,
moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lubbock, Idalou, Lubbock International Airport, and New Deal.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
